1 13. Must be an in - person school. A public charter school may not provide online, virtual, or
2 home education as the primary method of educational programming.
3 14. Is responsible for collecting, analyzing, and reporting student data from state
4 assessments administered by the superintendent of public instruction under section
5 15.1 - 21 - 08 in accordance with the performance framework in the approved charter
6 performance agreement.
7 15. Is subject to the public school approval requirements under section 15.1 - 06 - 06 .
8 Applicability of other laws, rules, and regulations.
9 1. Except as provided in this chapter, a public charter school is not subject to a state or
10 local law, rule, regulation, policy, or procedure related to education.
11 2. A public charter school is subject to federal laws and authorities related to education.
12 S uperintendent of public instruction - Information - Guidance - Rules .
13 The superintendent of public instruction :
14 1. S hall publish information and procedures regarding forming and operating a public
15 charter school and enrolling students in a public charter school.
16 2. May provide assistance and guidance for developing effective authorization and
17 oversight procedures.
18 3. Shall adopt rules in accordance with chapter 28 - 32 to implement this chapter .
19 Charter schools - Eligibility - Enrollment.
20 1. A prospective student is eligible to enroll in a public charter school if the prospective
21 student resides in the state.
22 2. A public charter school:
23 a. Shall enroll all students who wish to attend the school, unless the number of
24 students exceeds the enrollment capacity of a program, class, grade level, or
25 building.
26 b. Shall determine admission by a lottery if initial capacity is insufficient to enroll all
27 studen t s who timely submit an application. The selection process must take place
28 in a public setting. An applicant must have a fair opportunity to be selected in the
29 lottery. The lottery must be randomized and conducted competently,
30 transparently, and impartially.
