1 c. May not base admissions on ethnicity, national origin, religion, gender, income
2 level, disabling condition, proficiency in the English language, or academic or
3 athletic ability, except as provided under this section.
4 d. May limit enrollment to studen t s to a given age group, grade level, or pursuant to
5 a special emphasis stated in the school's application for a charter performance
6 agreement.
7 e. Shall give enrollment preference to studen t s and the siblings of students enrolled
8 in the public charter school the previous school year.
9 f. May give enrollment preference to children of a public charter school's
10 employees, if the students constitute no more than ten percent of the total
11 student population.
12 Superintendent of public instruction - Powers and duties - Report to the legislative
13 management.
14 1. The superintendent of public instruction shall:
15 a. Evaluate an application from the organizer of a proposed public charter school.
16 b. Deny an application that does not meet identified educational needs.
17 c. Determine whether a charter school application merits approval, conditional
18 approval, renewal, or revocation.
19 d. Negotiate and execute a charter performance agreement with an approved public
20 charter school.
21 e. Monitor the performance and compliance of a public charter school.
22 2. The superintendent of public instruction shall provide to the legislative management a
23 report within three years of approving the first public charter school summarizing the:
24 a. Strategic vision and progress of each public charter school.
25 b. Performance of each operating public charter school, according to the
26 performance measures and expectations specified in the charter performance
27 agreement.
28 c. Status of charter applications, including charter schools that were not approved,
29 not renewed, and closed.
30 d. Oversight and services provided by the superintendent of public instruction to
31 public charter schools.
