1 e. Total amount of fees collected from each public charter school, how the funds
2 were expended to support the public charter school, and the costs incurred by
3 the superintendent of public instruction to oversee each public charter school.
4 3. To cover costs of overseeing public charter schools in accordance with this chapter,
5 the superintendent of public instruction may:
6 a. Expend resources available to the department of public instruction, seek grant
7 funds, and establish partnerships.
8 b. Charge an administrative fee of up to three percent of annual per student
9 allocations received by each public charter school.
10 4. An employee of the superintendent of public instruction may not serve as an
11 employee, trustee, agent, representative, or vendor of a public charter school.
12 5. The superintendent of public instruction is not liable for the acts, omissions, debts, or
13 other obligations of a public charter school.
14 Establishment of a public charter school - Conversion to a public charter school -
15 Application requirements.
16 1. To establish a public charter school, the organizer of a public charter school shall
17 submit an application to the superintendent of public instruction and notify the board of
18 the school district where the public charter school will be located of the intent to
19 establish a public charter school.
20 2. For a school seeking to convert to a public charter school, the application must
21 demonstrate support for the proposed public charter school conversion with a petition
22 signed by a majority of teachers and parents or guardians of students at the existing
23 school. Students who attended the school before conversion to a public charter school
24 may be given enrollment preference.
25 3. The superintendent of public instruction shall create an application to establish a
26 public charter school or convert to a public charter school, which must include the
27 following essential elements:
28 a. School mission and vision.
29 b. Academic program.
30 c. Grade levels to be offered and growth plan.
31 d. Student evaluation plans.
