6 j. Student policies, including discipline plans.
7 k. Staff policies.
8 Education service providers.
9 If a proposed public charter school intends to enter an agreement with an education service
10 provider for education or management services, in addition to the other application
11 requirements, a public charter school organizer shall:
12 1. Explain the selection process and reasoning for selecting the education service
13 provider.
14 2. Provide evidence of the education service provider's success in serving student
15 populations similar to the targeted population, including demonstrated academic
16 achievement and, if applicable, successful management of nonacademic school
17 functions.
18 3. Provide information on the proposed duration of the service performance agreement,
19 roles, responsibilities, and scope of services and resources to be provided by the
20 education service provider, performance evaluation measures and timelines,
21 compensation structure, methods of performance agreement oversight and
22 enforcement, and conditions for renewal and termination of the performance
23 agreement.
24 4. Explain the relationship between the governing board, the school's leadership and
25 management team, and the education service provider, specifying how the governing
26 board and the school's leadership and management team will monitor and evaluate
27 the performance of the education service provider.
28 5. Provide a statement of assurance the governing board and the school's leadership
29 and management team are legally and operationally independent from the education
30 service provider.
