10 Application review process - Approval decisions.
11 1. The application review process must include a thorough evaluation of the application
12 and an in - person interview with the applicant at a public meeting .
13 2. The superintendent of public instruction shall:
14 a. Grant charters to applicants demonstrating competence in the charter
15 application.
16 b. Base decisions on documented evidence collected through the application review
17 process.
18 c. Follow charter granting policies and practices that are transparent, merit based,
19 and avoid a conflict of interest or the appearance of a conflict of interest.
20 3. No later than ninety days after the deadline for filing applications, the superintendent
21 of public instruction shall approve or deny each application. The superintendent of
22 public instruction shall publicly notice and publish public charter school application
23 decisions.
24 4. An approval decision may include reasonable conditions the applicant must meet
25 before a charter performance agreement may be executed. Reasonable conditions
26 may not include enrollment caps.
27 5. If the superintendent of public instruction conditionally approves or denies an
28 application, the superintendent of public instruction clearly shall state the reasons in
29 writing.
30 6. The superintendent of public instruction shall maintain a list of approved charter
31 applications in chronological order by date of approval.
