2 Charter performance agreements - Performance-based accountability - Data
3 reporting.
4 1. If an application is approved, the superintendent of public instruction and the
5 governing board of the public charter school shall execute a charter performance
6 agreement no later than sixty days after approval, including:
7 a. Academic, operational, and fiscal performance expectations and measures by
8 which the public charter school will be judged.
9 b. A description of the standards and processes under which the superintendent of
10 public instruction will oversee and monitor the public charter school.
11 c. Actions the superintendent of public instruction may pursue to revoke a charter
12 performance agreement.
13 2. A charter performance agreement must be signed by the superintendent of public
14 instruction and the public charter school's governing board.
15 3. A public charter school may not commence operations without a charter performance
16 agreement executed in accordance with this section and approved in a public meeting.
17 4. A public charter school governing board or its designee may negotiate with the
18 superintendent of public instruction to amend a charter performance agreement. The
19 superintendent of public instruction's review of the charter performance agreement
20 must be limited to the proposed request for amendments.
21 5. The charter performance agreement must include:
22 a. Indicators related to student academic proficiency, student academic growth,
23 attendance, recurrent enrollment, readiness for success upon graduation,
24 financial performance, governance performance, and family and community
25 engagement.
26 b. Annual performance targets to support the public charter school's compliance
27 with federal and state requirements.
28 6. More than one public charter school may be authorized under a charter performance
29 agreement as approved by the superintendent of public instruction, if the public charter
30 schools are separate and distinct from one another.
