1 Charter performance agreement - Terms - Delayed opening.
2 1. An initial charter performance agreement term is five years. The term commences on
3 the public charter school's first day of operation.
4 2. A public charter school may delay its opening for up to one school year after approval.
5 If the public charter school requires an opening delay of more than one school year,
6 the public charter school shall request an extension from the superintendent of public
7 instruction, which may be granted at the discretion of the superintendent.
8 3. The superintendent of public instruction may grant renewal of a charter performance
9 agreement for successive terms of five years.
10 Superintendent of public instruction - Monitoring - Annual evaluation - Opportunity
11 for remediation.
12 1. The superintendent of public instruction shall monitor the performance and legal
13 compliance of the public charter schools, including an annual evaluation for each
14 public charter school according to the charter performance agreement.
15 2. If a public charter school's performance or legal compliance is unsatisfactory, the
16 superintendent of public instruction promptly shall notify the public charter school and
17 provide a reasonable opportunity for the school to remedy the problems identified by
18 the superintendent of public instruction. A public charter school must be given at least
19 fifteen days to respond to the superintendent of public instruction's notification.
20 Public charter school performance report - Renewal responsibilities.
21 1. The superintendent of public instruction shall issue a public charter school
22 performance report for each five-year term of a charter performance agreement no
23 later than seventy-five days before a public charter school's fourth year of operation
24 begins.
25 2. The report must include renewal application guidance, as needed, and notice of any
26 concerns that may jeopardize the public charter school's position in seeking renewal if
27 not timely rectified.
28 3. A public charter school must be given at least thirty days to respond to the
29 performance report and submit any corrections or clarifications for the report.
