1 Renewal application - Decision.
2 1. The superintendent of public instruction shall create a uniform renewal application and
3 evaluation process.
4 2. The governing board shall submit a renewal application to the superintendent of public
5 instruction no later than the first day of instruction of a public charter school's final
6 authorized year of operation.
7 3. The renewal application must include:
8 a. A performance report and additional evidence in support of renewal.
9 b. Improvements undertaken or planned for the school.
10 c. Plans for the next charter term.
11 4. Renewal decisions must be supported by evidence of the public charter school's
12 performance under the performance framework in the charter performance agreement.
13 5. The superintendent of public instruction shall render a decision on a renewal
14 application no later than forty-five days after the renewal application was filed.
15 6. The public charter school is entitled to a public meeting with the superintendent of
16 public instruction regarding the renewal decision.
17 7. The superintendent of public instruction shall provide to the public charter school and
18 publish a report summarizing the basis for each decision, including supporting
19 evidence.
20 Charter performance agreement - Revocation - Nonrenewal.
21 1. A charter performance agreement may be revoked at any time or not renewed if the
22 superintendent of public instruction determines the public charter school:
23 a. Failed to comply with this chapter or other law.
24 b. Committed a material violation of a term, condition, standard, or procedure
25 required under the charter performance agreement.
26 c. Failed to meet or make sufficient progress toward the performance expectations
27 under the charter performance agreement.
28 d. Failed to meet accepted standards of fiscal management.
29 2. Revocation may not occur before a public meeting with the charter holder occurs,
30 unless the superintendent of public instruction determines the continued operation of
