8 School closure and dissolution.
9 If a public charter school intends to close and dissolve, the school shall:
10 1. Notify the parents or guardians of students of the intent to close and dissolve.
11 2. Transition students and student records as necessary.
12 3. Properly distribute the public charter school's assets, first to satisfy outstanding payroll
13 obligations for employees of the public charter school and then to other creditors of the
14 public charter school. If the assets of the public charter school are insufficient to pay
15 creditors, the distribution of assets may be determined by court order.
16 Local education agency status.
17 A public charter school:
18 1. Is a local education agency for purposes related to the funding of special education
19 services within the limits of legislative appropriations.
20 2. Shall provide services to students in public charter schools as required by federal,
21 state, and local law and the charter performance agreement.
22 Governing board.
23 1. A governing board:
24 a. May enter more than one charter performance agreement concurrently.
25 b. Shall adopt a viable conflict of interest policy and code of ethics.
26 c. Shall adopt a policy to avoid nepotism in hiring and supervision. The policy must
27 require disclosure to the board of potential nepotism in hiring and supervision. An
28 individual with a nepotism conflict may not be involved in the hiring decision or
29 supervision of an employee.
30 d. Shall have access to education service provider records to oversee the education
31 service provider contract.
