11 Generally accepted accounting principles - Independent audits.
12 A public charter school shall:
13 1. Adhere to generally accepted accounting principles.
14 2. Engage a qualified certified public accountant or public accountant to independently
15 audit the public charter school's finances once every six months. The public charter
16 school shall submit the audit to the superintendent of public instruction.
17 Funding - Categorical aid - Transportation.
18 1. A public charter school shall certify to the superintendent of public instruction its
19 student enrollment in accordance with section 15.1 - 27 - 02 .
20 2. The state shall pay to the public charter school the per-pupil state aid payment, which
21 is the dollar amount for the respective year under subsection 3 of section
22 15.1 - 27 - 04.1, for each student enrolled in the public charter school .
23 3. The state shall pay the proportionate share of moneys derived from federal and state
24 categorical aid programs to public charter schools with students or teachers who are
25 eligible for such aid. A public charter school that receives categorical aid shall comply
26 with related reporting requirements.
27 4. A public charter school may enter a contract with a local school district or private
28 provider to provide transportation to students of the public charter school.
29 5. Any moneys remaining in an account of a public charter school at the end of a budget
30 year must remain in the account for use by the public charter school during
